        h: `The big three priority polls`,
        body: `Every gym goer ranks bench, squat, and deadlift differently. Run a poll: "the most important lift for hypertrophy?", "the most enjoyable lift?", "the lift you skip most?". Anonymous so the squat-skip secret can come out. Aggregate the result and you'll see your gym chat split into camps — the lower body crew, the upper body crew, and the deadlift sole-believers. The poll round is the most efficient way to map your friend group's lifting religion. Then run a sub-poll: "which lift has the worst injury risk?" and you've got hours of follow-up debate fuel.`,
