        body: `Minecraft servers have a lifecycle. Every six to twelve months the community debates a world reset, a mode change, a new modpack. Run a poll: "reset the survival world?", "switch to Hardcore for next season?", "try the new modpack?", "vanilla or modded next season?". Anonymous voting lets newer members vote without being intimidated by the loud OG voices. The result is the community's actual will, not just the loudest opinions. Use the poll outcome as the official decision and the admin team has cover from accusations of favoritism. The polls institutionalize fair governance.`,
